# NO AUTOMATIC SCRAPING RULE

## CRITICAL - VIOLATION PROHIBITED

**NO automatic scraping of any external data sources is allowed under any circumstances.**

## Prohibited Actions:

❌ **Cron jobs** - No scheduled scraping tasks
❌ **Background schedulers** - No automatic refresh jobs
❌ **Auto-refresh timers** - No periodic data fetching
❌ **Systemd services** - No daemon-based scraping
❌ **API auto-refresh** - No automatic refresh on startup
❌ **Webhook triggers** - No external trigger-based scraping

## Allowed Actions:

✅ **Manual user triggers only** - Scraping must be initiated by explicit user action
✅ **Admin "Test Scrape" button** - Only through designated manual UI controls
✅ **Rate-limited manual** - Must respect site rate limits and terms of service

## Enforcement:

- All automatic scraping code must be disabled or removed
- Frontend auto-refresh intervals must be set to `false`
- Background schedulers must be disabled (`SKIP_BACKGROUND_SCHEDULER=1`)
- No cron jobs for scraping
- Manual scraping only through admin interface

## Reason:

Previous automatic scraping resulted in account bans. All data collection must be user-controlled to avoid violating terms of service and getting banned.

## Testing:

App testing must use the manual "Test Scrape" button in Settings → Admin to verify scraping functionality works when explicitly requested by the user.

